Article 1.2:
Interfaces (Polymorphism):
This will ask as abstact class 
In Go, interfaces define a set of method signatures but do not contain any implementation. 
Any type that implements all the methods of an interface is said to satisfy that interface, 
allowing polymorphism (the ability to use different types interchangeably).


